WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.000
Bring it!

2
00:00:05.850 --> 00:00:08.440
Ushiwaka's amazing...

3
00:00:08.720 --> 00:00:10.400
I'm excited.

4
00:00:10.400 --> 00:00:11.400
All right, here we go!

5
00:00:19.670 --> 00:00:21.560
Well hello, left.

6
00:00:42.310 --> 00:00:48.980
Haikyu!!

7
00:00:42.310 --> 00:00:48.980
Karasuno High School vs Shiratorizawa Academy

8
00:01:53.050 --> 00:01:55.460
Shiratorizawa               Karasuno

9
00:01:53.880 --> 00:01:57.670
Nice kill, Ushijima!

10
00:01:55.460 --> 00:02:00.470
Be Courageous Warriors

11
00:01:55.630 --> 00:02:00.220
Episode 02: The Threat of the "Left"

12
00:01:58.280 --> 00:02:01.750
Ushijima! Ushijima!

13
00:02:01.750 --> 00:02:03.680
Nishinoya-kun...

14
00:02:03.680 --> 00:02:05.770
Don't mind! Next, next!

15
00:02:05.770 --> 00:02:06.640
Yeah.

16
00:02:06.640 --> 00:02:08.230
Don't mind!

17
00:02:08.230 --> 00:02:09.350
Next, next!

18
00:02:09.860 --> 00:02:10.920
Nice serve!

19
00:02:13.740 --> 00:02:14.500
Out!

20
00:02:17.680 --> 00:02:18.630
Yes!

21
00:02:19.090 --> 00:02:19.920
Sorry!

22
00:02:19.920 --> 00:02:21.160
Nice serve, Taichi!

23
00:02:25.240 --> 00:02:27.000
Kawanishi, one more! Nice serve!

24
00:02:28.950 --> 00:02:29.930
Got it!

25
00:02:28.950 --> 00:02:29.930
Tanaka-san!

26
00:02:32.920 --> 00:02:33.790
Sorry!

27
00:02:33.790 --> 00:02:34.440
My bad.

28
00:02:34.440 --> 00:02:35.300
Don't mind!

29
00:02:34.440 --> 00:02:36.690
Are they nervous after all?

30
00:02:36.690 --> 00:02:38.760
Their movements are stiff...

31
00:02:38.760 --> 00:02:41.470
Shiratorizawa           Karasuno

32
00:02:40.360 --> 00:02:41.100
it.

33
00:02:42.000 --> 00:02:43.930
We need to hurry up and regroup 
or it'll be too late...

34
00:02:43.930 --> 00:02:46.140
Calm down!

35
00:02:46.560 --> 00:02:48.810
There's no time to self-destruct!

36
00:02:48.810 --> 00:02:50.090
U-Um...

37
00:02:48.810 --> 00:02:51.160
What are you so 
nervous about?! The TV crews?

38
00:02:51.160 --> 00:02:53.980
Quit messing around!

39
00:02:55.390 --> 00:02:58.110
Got it! We got it, Suga, so calm down!

40
00:02:58.110 --> 00:03:00.280
Suga-san's scary...

41
00:02:58.840 --> 00:03:00.280
I'm so sorry!

42
00:03:00.820 --> 00:03:05.950
Someone gets far more agitated than the players
 and it helps calm them down...

43
00:03:05.950 --> 00:03:07.990
I don't care what the circumstance is.

44
00:03:07.990 --> 00:03:10.250
I just need them to score once
 and build momentum.

45
00:03:10.610 --> 00:03:14.210
Crap... He totally glared at me...

46
00:03:17.450 --> 00:03:18.890
Nice serve! One more!

47
00:03:19.630 --> 00:03:20.660
Got it!

48
00:03:21.710 --> 00:03:23.640
Yes! It went up nicely!

49
00:03:23.640 --> 00:03:24.680
Go!

50
00:03:26.810 --> 00:03:28.220
Nice receive!

51
00:03:29.280 --> 00:03:30.270
Wakatoshi!

52
00:03:33.290 --> 00:03:34.810
All right!

53
00:03:37.000 --> 00:03:38.940
Don't mind! Next, next!

54
00:03:38.440 --> 00:03:40.520
Ushijima!

55
00:03:41.260 --> 00:03:44.450
Ushijima! Ushijima!

56
00:03:42.380 --> 00:03:43.640
Give me three.

57
00:03:46.520 --> 00:03:49.060
I promise I'll get used to it.

58
00:03:52.520 --> 00:03:55.750
Huh? I thought something was weird!

59
00:03:56.150 --> 00:03:57.460
One more!

60
00:03:56.150 --> 00:03:58.170
Their #1 is left-handed?

61
00:03:58.460 --> 00:04:00.970
So that's why he approaches from the right.

62
00:04:00.970 --> 00:04:03.180
Ryu always goes in from the left.

63
00:04:03.470 --> 00:04:04.820
Yeah.

64
00:04:04.820 --> 00:04:08.570
Man... talk about a chosen ace.

65
00:04:09.390 --> 00:04:23.360
Opposite

66
00:04:09.390 --> 00:04:23.360
Setter

67
00:04:09.880 --> 00:04:12.940
Ushiwaka's position is called “opposite,”

68
00:04:12.940 --> 00:04:15.370
and they're diagonal from the setter.

69
00:04:15.370 --> 00:04:18.310
On Karasuno's side, it's where Sawamura is.

70
00:04:18.310 --> 00:04:20.620
Depending on how the player 
in that position plays,

71
00:04:20.620 --> 00:04:23.360
the way the whole team plays changes.

72
00:04:23.360 --> 00:04:26.220
One pattern is to have a 
player like Sawamura there,

73
00:04:23.740 --> 00:04:24.680
Got it!

74
00:04:25.170 --> 00:04:26.120
All right!

75
00:04:26.120 --> 00:04:27.800
Nice, Daichi-san!

76
00:04:26.220 --> 00:04:29.580
who's a player that's skilled 
all-around, and good at defense.

77
00:04:27.800 --> 00:04:29.030
Left!

78
00:04:29.580 --> 00:04:31.580
That's pretty common on high school teams.

79
00:04:31.960 --> 00:04:35.540
The other pattern is to have 
a cannon like Ushiwaka there.

80
00:04:33.860 --> 00:04:35.000
Nice receive!

81
00:04:36.070 --> 00:04:38.190
They don't serve or receive,

82
00:04:38.190 --> 00:04:40.300
and are always prepared to attack,

83
00:04:40.300 --> 00:04:43.240
from either the front or back line.

84
00:04:43.240 --> 00:04:44.510
A while back,

85
00:04:44.760 --> 00:04:47.020
they were called super aces.

86
00:04:50.490 --> 00:04:54.170
Nice kill, Ushijima!

87
00:04:54.900 --> 00:04:58.140
Ushijima! Ushijima!

88
00:04:56.290 --> 00:05:00.650
I get that Ushiwaka guy is 
super tall and super strong,

89
00:05:00.650 --> 00:05:03.200
but does the fact that he's 
left-handed make him that—

90
00:05:03.200 --> 00:05:04.480
Bring it!

91
00:05:07.200 --> 00:05:10.410
All right!

92
00:05:07.890 --> 00:05:09.850
All right!

93
00:05:10.410 --> 00:05:12.360
All right!

94
00:05:11.330 --> 00:05:12.870
Tanaka, nice kill!

95
00:05:12.870 --> 00:05:17.120
Go, go, Karasuno! Push it, push it, Karasuno!

96
00:05:17.120 --> 00:05:19.340
Shiratorizawa           Karasuno

97
00:05:17.120 --> 00:05:21.080
Go, go, Karasuno! Push it, push it, Karasuno!

98
00:05:19.680 --> 00:05:21.720
We finally got a point in...

99
00:05:21.720 --> 00:05:23.690
Way to go, Ryu!

100
00:05:23.690 --> 00:05:26.490
So, what's so special about the lefty?

101
00:05:27.300 --> 00:05:31.060
Since they go up against people who 
are right-handed way more often,

102
00:05:31.590 --> 00:05:34.940
playing against someone who's 
left-handed is unbelievably difficult.

103
00:05:35.520 --> 00:05:39.060
For example, when a single blocker goes up,

104
00:05:39.060 --> 00:05:41.600
they jump up facing their 
opponent's dominant hand.

105
00:05:41.600 --> 00:05:45.240
Which means they're about 
a shoulder's width away.

106
00:05:45.580 --> 00:05:48.040
So unless the attack is a very simple one,

107
00:05:46.230 --> 00:05:48.040
Asahi-san, nice serve!

108
00:05:48.040 --> 00:05:50.070
the showdown is over in a moment.

109
00:05:50.950 --> 00:05:53.660
If they jump up in a way 
their body is used to...

110
00:05:54.410 --> 00:05:55.590
Time difference...

111
00:05:58.370 --> 00:06:00.500
...they'll end up missing, no matter what.

112
00:06:00.500 --> 00:06:04.160
Nice kill, Ushijima!

113
00:06:00.780 --> 00:06:02.490
What are they doing?

114
00:06:02.490 --> 00:06:04.710
Karasuno's blocks are full of holes!

115
00:06:05.000 --> 00:06:08.430
Ushijima! Ushijima!

116
00:06:05.620 --> 00:06:08.430
It's not just the fact that he's 
left-handed that makes him strong.

117
00:06:08.790 --> 00:06:12.580
Not only is he left-handed, 
but his strength is also top-tier.

118
00:06:09.000 --> 00:06:12.860
Wakatoshi-kun, nice kill!
I see you're as sharp as ever.

119
00:06:12.860 --> 00:06:13.660
Yeah.

120
00:06:13.030 --> 00:06:15.140
That's what Ushiwaka is.

121
00:06:15.420 --> 00:06:18.680
So they already scored four straight 
points because of Ushijima-kun.

122
00:06:19.160 --> 00:06:19.850
Yeah.

123
00:06:20.270 --> 00:06:22.920
Their setter seems to have solid hands,

124
00:06:21.680 --> 00:06:22.920
Rotate! Rotate!

125
00:06:22.920 --> 00:06:24.170
Right!

126
00:06:22.920 --> 00:06:26.820
and I'm sure he'd like to 
get some in from the get-go.

127
00:06:26.820 --> 00:06:29.280
Japanese National High School Volleyball Tournament

128
00:06:29.280 --> 00:06:31.740
Shiratorizawa               Karasuno

129
00:06:32.050 --> 00:06:33.790
Huh? What's that buzzer for?

130
00:06:33.790 --> 00:06:36.760
Oh, this is a technical time out.

131
00:06:34.490 --> 00:06:36.760
Shiratorizawa!

132
00:06:36.760 --> 00:06:37.950
What's that?

133
00:06:37.950 --> 00:06:40.310
Shiratorizawa!

134
00:06:37.950 --> 00:06:40.970
It's a time-out that only 
happens during five-set matches,

135
00:06:40.970 --> 00:06:44.810
when one of the teams
 hits 8 or 16 points...

136
00:06:41.520 --> 00:06:43.700
Shiratorizawa!

137
00:06:44.810 --> 00:06:45.710
Apparently.

138
00:06:44.970 --> 00:06:47.060
Shiratorizawa!

139
00:06:46.100 --> 00:06:47.310
Huh...

140
00:06:48.080 --> 00:06:51.210
Blocking all comes down to timing!

141
00:06:48.420 --> 00:06:50.470
Shiratorizawa!

142
00:06:51.210 --> 00:06:54.650
If they get through the top, it'll be 
difficult to prepare to receive, as well.

143
00:06:51.800 --> 00:06:53.960
Shiratorizawa!

144
00:06:54.650 --> 00:06:56.540
You need to touch the ball, 
even if you can't stop it!

145
00:06:55.220 --> 00:06:57.580
Shiratorizawa!

146
00:06:56.540 --> 00:06:59.140
Make Ushijima feel that there's a wall.

147
00:06:58.720 --> 00:07:00.860
Shiratorizawa!

148
00:06:59.420 --> 00:07:00.470
Right!

149
00:07:02.600 --> 00:07:04.570
Japanese National High School Volleyball Tournament

150
00:07:02.600 --> 00:07:04.570
Fly

151
00:07:02.600 --> 00:07:04.570
Be Courageous Warriors

152
00:07:11.200 --> 00:07:12.280
One touch!

153
00:07:12.840 --> 00:07:13.750
!

154
00:07:14.120 --> 00:07:15.580
Wow...

155
00:07:14.120 --> 00:07:16.330
Shiratorizawa               Karasuno

156
00:07:15.960 --> 00:07:17.950
Ushijima!

157
00:07:16.790 --> 00:07:19.290
Ushiwaka's unstoppable.

158
00:07:18.760 --> 00:07:21.500
Ushijima! Ushijima!

159
00:07:19.630 --> 00:07:21.500
Don't mind! Get the next one!

160
00:07:21.860 --> 00:07:23.980
That's it! Just keep that up!

161
00:07:24.600 --> 00:07:26.560
Keep letting him know that 
there's a wall there.

162
00:07:26.560 --> 00:07:28.460
Then a path will open up!

163
00:07:30.360 --> 00:07:32.180
Shiratorizawa has Ushiwaka.

164
00:07:33.030 --> 00:07:33.770
Then...

165
00:07:34.410 --> 00:07:37.100
Karasuno has me.

166
00:07:39.700 --> 00:07:40.900
Right.

167
00:07:41.330 --> 00:07:43.720
Stopping all of Ushijima's attacks,

168
00:07:43.720 --> 00:07:46.490
or even picking them all up, is impossible.

169
00:07:47.160 --> 00:07:47.820
But...

170
00:07:47.820 --> 00:07:51.950
Ushijima




     Block










Nishinoya

171
00:07:48.820 --> 00:07:51.950
All you've got to do is make those 
impossible spikes possible.

172
00:07:52.440 --> 00:07:53.240
Hm?

173
00:07:54.030 --> 00:07:55.700
Total defense.

174
00:07:55.700 --> 00:08:05.420
Ushijima

175
00:07:55.700 --> 00:08:05.420
Block

176
00:07:55.700 --> 00:08:05.420
Nishinoya

177
00:07:56.640 --> 00:08:00.090
Ushijima's really good at angle shots, 
as we've seen in past games,

178
00:08:00.090 --> 00:08:02.510
so we're going to tighten up
 our block on those,

179
00:08:02.510 --> 00:08:05.420
and place Nishinoya where the now 
opened straight path would be.

180
00:08:06.050 --> 00:08:08.420
We're going to set it up so 
he's hitting to our libero.

181
00:08:13.060 --> 00:08:14.380
Nice timing!

182
00:08:23.440 --> 00:08:26.360
Be Courageous Warriors

183
00:08:23.440 --> 00:08:27.420
Nice kill, Ushijima!

184
00:08:26.360 --> 00:08:28.820
Shiratorizawa               Karasuno

185
00:08:27.980 --> 00:08:31.180
Ushijima! Ushijima!

186
00:08:33.750 --> 00:08:37.370
If Yu can't pick those up, 
he's going to be impossible to handle.

187
00:08:37.680 --> 00:08:40.260
I think it's because of the spin.

188
00:08:40.260 --> 00:08:40.830
Hm?

189
00:08:41.560 --> 00:08:43.290
Spiking left-handed means

190
00:08:43.290 --> 00:08:47.790
the ball will spin differently 
than spiking right-handed.

191
00:08:48.440 --> 00:08:51.000
Volleyball is a sport where 
you can't hold the ball,

192
00:08:51.000 --> 00:08:54.120
and the space to capture
it is extremely narrow.

193
00:08:54.580 --> 00:08:56.460
So the moment you capture the ball,

194
00:08:56.460 --> 00:08:59.370
if the way it hits your hands 
is even a tiny bit off,

195
00:08:59.370 --> 00:09:01.370
it causes a huge deviation.

196
00:09:08.400 --> 00:09:09.830
Chance ball!

197
00:09:10.280 --> 00:09:11.860
! I'm sorry!

198
00:09:15.810 --> 00:09:17.180
Our timing was too fast...

199
00:09:24.540 --> 00:09:26.750
Shiratorizawa               Karasuno

200
00:09:27.080 --> 00:09:30.700
Nice kill, Ushijima!

201
00:09:27.270 --> 00:09:29.210
It may be called total defense,

202
00:09:29.650 --> 00:09:33.210
but even just getting our 
timing down isn't easy.

203
00:09:31.480 --> 00:09:34.750
Ushijima! Ushijima!

204
00:09:33.720 --> 00:09:36.240
Concentrate on number one!

205
00:09:36.240 --> 00:09:38.970
Do you think you'll be able 
to stop Ushiwaka's spikes?

206
00:09:42.740 --> 00:09:45.290
There's no way that I can beat Ushiwaka.

207
00:09:50.730 --> 00:09:51.740
All right!

208
00:09:51.740 --> 00:09:53.900
I've been focusing too much on Ushiwaka.

209
00:09:53.900 --> 00:09:58.110
Shiratorizawa           Karasuno

210
00:09:55.010 --> 00:09:58.110
Kawanishi! Kawanishi!

211
00:09:55.400 --> 00:09:58.110
Is that kid with the glasses even trying?

212
00:09:58.530 --> 00:10:00.680
He needs to show some more 
of that fighting spirit!

213
00:10:00.680 --> 00:10:01.580
Fighting spirit!

214
00:10:01.580 --> 00:10:05.360
They're sneaking in some quicks really well.

215
00:10:05.360 --> 00:10:08.410
They've gotta hurry and do something 
about the left-handed guy.

216
00:10:08.410 --> 00:10:11.360
I guess there's not much they can 
do about how much they're used

217
00:10:11.360 --> 00:10:13.460
to right-handed shots.

218
00:10:17.600 --> 00:10:19.040
All right!

219
00:10:17.970 --> 00:10:19.040
Sorry!

220
00:10:19.040 --> 00:10:19.760
Don't mind.

221
00:10:19.040 --> 00:10:20.730
At the very least,

222
00:10:20.730 --> 00:10:22.510
he's the exact opposite 
from the kind of player

223
00:10:22.510 --> 00:10:24.380
that moves based on sensations.

224
00:10:25.310 --> 00:10:26.560
Nice serve!

225
00:10:26.560 --> 00:10:29.020
He doesn't believe in his own strength.

226
00:10:29.600 --> 00:10:31.790
And he doesn't trust the senses he's built up.

227
00:10:31.790 --> 00:10:32.790
Nice receive!

228
00:10:35.140 --> 00:10:37.070
How could you say that?! 
You're his older brother!

229
00:10:37.070 --> 00:10:38.240
I'm complimenting him!

230
00:10:38.850 --> 00:10:40.510
You see, with my brother,

231
00:10:40.510 --> 00:10:42.700
the more he feels let down, 
the calmer he gets.

232
00:10:42.700 --> 00:10:46.410
He only believes in the information
 that his eyes can see.

233
00:10:48.130 --> 00:10:48.790
Got it.

234
00:11:00.470 --> 00:11:02.720
Shiratorizawa               Karasuno

235
00:11:04.400 --> 00:11:07.260
Kei was in the path of the spike right now.

236
00:11:07.260 --> 00:11:09.640
He was also positioned correctly on the left.

237
00:11:09.640 --> 00:11:10.810
So why...

238
00:11:12.160 --> 00:11:13.690
You were so close, Nishinoya!

239
00:11:13.690 --> 00:11:16.110
You're actually able to 
react to Ushiwaka's spikes!

240
00:11:16.110 --> 00:11:18.170
The spike that I was actually able to touch

241
00:11:18.170 --> 00:11:19.930
is definitely not his full strength.

242
00:11:20.910 --> 00:11:23.600
He's probably still warming up his engine,

243
00:11:23.600 --> 00:11:28.360
and concentrating on getting 
his spikes over our blocks.

244
00:11:28.360 --> 00:11:30.060
I remember in middle school,

245
00:11:30.060 --> 00:11:34.040
getting passes from a guy that 
was left-handed was really hard.

246
00:11:34.440 --> 00:11:35.900
So apparently with Ushiwaka's shots...

247
00:11:35.900 --> 00:11:38.120
his off-speed shots are killer, too.

248
00:11:41.080 --> 00:11:43.050
Tsukki, man, you jammed your finger?
Are you okay?

249
00:11:43.720 --> 00:11:46.870
Did you have to rhyme that?

250
00:11:46.870 --> 00:11:48.680
I'll do it. Let me see.

251
00:11:48.680 --> 00:11:49.390
Thank you.

252
00:11:49.970 --> 00:11:51.880
This isn't any different from the usual.

253
00:11:51.880 --> 00:11:52.970
Actually,

254
00:11:52.970 --> 00:11:55.640
if it just stays like this, we'll be lucky.

255
00:11:56.850 --> 00:11:57.630
There you go.

256
00:11:57.630 --> 00:11:58.590
Thank you.

257
00:11:59.990 --> 00:12:01.860
Did I hesitate back there?

258
00:12:02.880 --> 00:12:05.820
No... I thought that I would lose.

259
00:12:06.440 --> 00:12:08.620
As if that was without a doubt.

260
00:12:16.170 --> 00:12:19.070
Guys! Your faces are stiff!

261
00:12:19.070 --> 00:12:21.240
Relax! Relax! Rel—

262
00:12:21.920 --> 00:12:23.130
...ax.

263
00:12:27.370 --> 00:12:30.620
Ushijima-kun's serves were pretty 
amazing, too, weren't they?

264
00:12:31.060 --> 00:12:35.340
He doesn't have monster precision 
or control like Oikawa,

265
00:12:35.340 --> 00:12:37.690
but his impact speaks for itself.

266
00:12:50.390 --> 00:12:51.750
Nice serve!

267
00:12:53.640 --> 00:12:55.260
I don't get it...

268
00:12:55.720 --> 00:12:57.430
What's with that guy?

269
00:12:57.960 --> 00:12:59.870
If they get any farther ahead of us,

270
00:12:59.170 --> 00:13:02.130
Shiratorizawa           Karasuno

271
00:12:59.870 --> 00:13:01.800
it'll be hard on them mentally, too.

272
00:13:02.400 --> 00:13:04.030
Sorry! We'll get the next one!

273
00:13:04.030 --> 00:13:04.900
Right!

274
00:13:05.720 --> 00:13:08.490
Thank goodness I'm not in 
position to receive a serve.

275
00:13:09.100 --> 00:13:12.030
Trying to get that serve 
head-on is crazy,

276
00:13:12.030 --> 00:13:15.350
and it's like the whole gym is 
cheering for Shiratorizawa.

277
00:13:16.210 --> 00:13:19.170
We're probably going to have 
to give up this first set,

278
00:13:19.170 --> 00:13:19.930
and then...

279
00:13:21.350 --> 00:13:22.490
Bring it.

280
00:13:23.280 --> 00:13:25.740
Bring it! Bring it!

281
00:13:26.840 --> 00:13:30.220
Bring it! Bring it! Bring it!

282
00:13:27.460 --> 00:13:28.450
One more!

283
00:13:30.220 --> 00:13:31.630
Bring it to me!

284
00:13:32.250 --> 00:13:34.760
Come on, bring it!

285
00:13:49.490 --> 00:13:51.660
It went up!

286
00:13:53.100 --> 00:13:59.940
Haikyu!!
Karasuno High School vs Shiratorizawa Academy

287
00:14:00.020 --> 00:14:06.950
Haikyu!!
Karasuno High School vs Shiratorizawa Academy

288
00:14:14.360 --> 00:14:16.330
It went up!

289
00:14:16.330 --> 00:14:17.770
All right! Perfect!

290
00:14:17.770 --> 00:14:19.040
Finish it!

291
00:14:20.580 --> 00:14:22.040
Is he planning to hit it?

292
00:14:26.350 --> 00:14:28.300
All right!

293
00:14:28.630 --> 00:14:30.460
Nice toss, Kageyama!

294
00:14:30.460 --> 00:14:33.260
I totally thought Kageyama 
was going to spike it...

295
00:14:33.530 --> 00:14:36.280
He definitely did what he said he'd do.

296
00:14:36.280 --> 00:14:37.480
We can't just stand around.

297
00:14:40.660 --> 00:14:43.530
He went to set from a spike motion.

298
00:14:43.530 --> 00:14:45.480
Nothing less from Oikawa's junior.

299
00:14:45.480 --> 00:14:47.470
Huh? He is?!

300
00:14:47.470 --> 00:14:48.900
That sucks!

301
00:14:48.900 --> 00:14:52.600
You seem pretty relaxed, considering 
we're playing against Shiratorizawa.

302
00:14:52.600 --> 00:14:53.730
Well,

303
00:14:53.730 --> 00:14:56.170
no one scares me more than
 Oikawa-san for the time being.

304
00:14:56.940 --> 00:14:58.060
I see!

305
00:14:59.600 --> 00:15:01.770
All right! Time to fight back!

306
00:15:05.510 --> 00:15:07.150
Shoyo came out!

307
00:15:07.150 --> 00:15:08.970
The first time he came out,

308
00:15:08.970 --> 00:15:11.740
he was immediately rotated out.

309
00:15:11.740 --> 00:15:13.290
Get one in there!

310
00:15:13.290 --> 00:15:14.520
Nice serve!

311
00:15:15.110 --> 00:15:17.240
Man, he's really short.

312
00:15:17.240 --> 00:15:19.730
And he's somehow a middle 
blocker despite that.

313
00:15:27.150 --> 00:15:28.500
Nice receive!

314
00:15:27.150 --> 00:15:30.060
You're right! He really won't go for serves.

315
00:15:30.060 --> 00:15:32.110
He's getting ready for a back attack.

316
00:15:36.160 --> 00:15:37.760
All right!

317
00:15:36.660 --> 00:15:38.250
One person's time difference...

318
00:15:38.920 --> 00:15:40.580
Yay!

319
00:15:43.120 --> 00:15:46.170
Tendo! Tendo!

320
00:15:44.210 --> 00:15:46.170
Shiratorizawa           Karasuno

321
00:15:47.460 --> 00:15:48.730
Nice serve!

322
00:15:51.120 --> 00:15:51.840
Out!

323
00:15:53.550 --> 00:15:54.830
All right!

324
00:15:54.830 --> 00:15:56.300
Nice call!

325
00:15:56.300 --> 00:15:59.470
It's not that Shiratorizawa
 isn't making any mistakes.

326
00:15:59.470 --> 00:16:00.770
We can break through!

327
00:16:06.790 --> 00:16:08.320
All right!

328
00:16:08.320 --> 00:16:09.290
Yes!

329
00:16:09.290 --> 00:16:11.610
The fact that Kageyama and Nishinoya 
are playing like they normally do

330
00:16:09.890 --> 00:16:11.700
Nice serve, Kageyama!

331
00:16:11.610 --> 00:16:13.760
is nothing less than amazing.

332
00:16:13.760 --> 00:16:14.530
Yes.

333
00:16:21.720 --> 00:16:22.540
Goshiki!

334
00:16:25.960 --> 00:16:29.170
All right!

335
00:16:26.650 --> 00:16:28.260
All right!

336
00:16:29.830 --> 00:16:32.880
Did you see my super straight shot?!

337
00:16:33.240 --> 00:16:34.540
Nice receive.

338
00:16:34.540 --> 00:16:36.460
Nah, I wasn't able to return it properly.

339
00:16:36.460 --> 00:16:38.280
Don't you get tired of 
competing for attention?

340
00:16:36.460 --> 00:16:38.850
That kid's pretty strong for a first-year.

341
00:16:39.840 --> 00:16:41.570
Let's go, Kageyama.

342
00:16:41.570 --> 00:16:42.310
Yeah.

343
00:16:42.310 --> 00:16:44.270
Shiratorizawa           Karasuno

344
00:16:49.760 --> 00:16:50.610
Ushijima-san!

345
00:16:54.760 --> 00:16:56.660
All right! He got it!

346
00:16:57.120 --> 00:16:58.760
! I didn't catch it completely.

347
00:16:59.890 --> 00:17:01.240
Hinata, get the last!

348
00:17:05.040 --> 00:17:06.400
He hit it against the block!

349
00:17:06.400 --> 00:17:07.670
That was a great rebound!

350
00:17:08.740 --> 00:17:10.050
Once more! Once more!

351
00:17:14.720 --> 00:17:15.550
Huh?

352
00:17:16.740 --> 00:17:20.040
I'm Hinata Shoyo, from the concrete.

353
00:17:21.000 --> 00:17:24.270
I'm going to beat you, and go to nationals.

354
00:17:32.570 --> 00:17:35.530
So he knows how to receive, too?!

355
00:17:36.660 --> 00:17:37.990
Give it to me.

356
00:17:39.560 --> 00:17:40.530
Ushijima-san!

357
00:17:48.420 --> 00:17:51.420
Be Courageous Warriors

358
00:17:51.420 --> 00:17:54.630
Shiratorizawa           Karasuno

359
00:17:51.970 --> 00:17:53.610
All right!

360
00:17:58.050 --> 00:18:01.390
Wow, Wakatoshi-kun, 
who's only interested in himself,

361
00:18:01.390 --> 00:18:03.500
is actually competing with someone.

362
00:18:03.920 --> 00:18:05.350
How amusing!

363
00:18:07.350 --> 00:18:09.470
It's not over yet!
It's just the beginning!

364
00:18:09.470 --> 00:18:10.560
Switch it up!

365
00:18:12.000 --> 00:18:13.020
Next, next!

366
00:18:13.330 --> 00:18:16.870
Wakatoshi-kun, do you know Karasuno's #10?

367
00:18:17.400 --> 00:18:18.770
I met him on the street.

368
00:18:18.770 --> 00:18:19.830
The street?

369
00:18:19.830 --> 00:18:22.600
He said that he was going to 
beat me and go to nationals.

370
00:18:22.600 --> 00:18:24.220
What?! In the street?

371
00:18:24.660 --> 00:18:26.490
No, not in the street.

372
00:18:27.360 --> 00:18:29.040
Come to think of it, Ushijima-san,

373
00:18:29.040 --> 00:18:32.160
didn't you get in trouble for letting 
outsiders onto school grounds?

374
00:18:32.160 --> 00:18:35.040
Karasuno's #10 is so amusing!

375
00:18:35.040 --> 00:18:36.600
So that's why you like him.

376
00:18:36.600 --> 00:18:37.950
No, I dislike him.

377
00:18:37.950 --> 00:18:38.720
Huh?

378
00:18:39.910 --> 00:18:42.140
I hate confidence that has no basis.

379
00:18:43.080 --> 00:18:46.140
Oh? This is even more rare.

380
00:18:46.690 --> 00:18:49.360
Considering he's making 
Wakatoshi-kun say such things,

381
00:18:49.360 --> 00:18:51.960
sounds like he'll entertain me.

382
00:18:53.320 --> 00:18:56.110
I guess I'll work hard, too.

383
00:18:57.640 --> 00:18:59.480
There's no reason to panic.

384
00:18:59.480 --> 00:19:02.820
They just happened to take 
the first of five matches.

385
00:19:03.140 --> 00:19:05.070
And about this match...

386
00:19:05.070 --> 00:19:07.680
Ushijima scored eleven points,

387
00:19:07.680 --> 00:19:10.040
so he scored almost half of the points.

388
00:19:11.030 --> 00:19:14.490
But the fact that the ball 
is going to Ushijima so often

389
00:19:14.490 --> 00:19:17.760
means that you're frustrating 
 Shiratorizawa that much.

390
00:19:18.360 --> 00:19:20.540
Ushijima is also human.

391
00:19:20.540 --> 00:19:22.720
He'll eventually reach 
the end of his stamina.

392
00:19:23.250 --> 00:19:25.390
He'll eventually start 
to feel even the attacks

393
00:19:25.390 --> 00:19:27.520
that he's not making himself.

394
00:19:27.520 --> 00:19:28.460
Don't forget that!

395
00:19:28.460 --> 00:19:29.290
Right!

396
00:19:29.680 --> 00:19:31.900
Shiratorizawa               Karasuno

397
00:19:32.210 --> 00:19:33.910
Bring it!

398
00:19:34.720 --> 00:19:36.860
You better get one from the start, Tsutomu!

399
00:19:36.860 --> 00:19:37.570
Right!

400
00:19:43.400 --> 00:19:44.030
Good.

401
00:19:48.870 --> 00:19:51.120
Synchronized attack!

402
00:19:51.120 --> 00:19:53.330
The four of them are attacking at once?

403
00:19:59.360 --> 00:20:00.970
All right!

404
00:19:59.730 --> 00:20:00.970
Yes!

405
00:20:00.970 --> 00:20:08.880
Go, go, Karasuno! Push it, push it, Karasuno!

406
00:20:04.270 --> 00:20:06.380
So they tricked us.

407
00:20:06.380 --> 00:20:07.560
That's troublesome.

408
00:20:07.930 --> 00:20:09.890
Shiratorizawa           Karasuno

409
00:20:09.890 --> 00:20:11.620
Daichi-san, nice serve!

410
00:20:12.760 --> 00:20:13.750
Got it!

411
00:20:14.310 --> 00:20:15.720
Nice receive!

412
00:20:18.020 --> 00:20:18.940
Nice.

413
00:20:18.940 --> 00:20:19.980
Yup.

414
00:20:20.530 --> 00:20:22.090
In the case of Shiratorizawa,

415
00:20:22.090 --> 00:20:25.710
the fact that they're going for the center 
line without using Ushijima is showing

416
00:20:25.710 --> 00:20:27.160
that they have the upper hand.

417
00:20:27.240 --> 00:20:34.460
Ushijima (WS)     Kawanishi (MB)     Goshiki (WS)
Ohira (WS)          Tendo (MB)          Shirabu (S)

418
00:20:27.570 --> 00:20:30.810
And if the center line starts functioning,

419
00:20:30.810 --> 00:20:34.460
we're not going to be able to handle Ushijima,
 or their other wing spikers.

420
00:20:36.150 --> 00:20:37.660
All right!

421
00:20:37.660 --> 00:20:38.600
Nice kill!

422
00:20:38.600 --> 00:20:43.880
Our most difficult problem in 
this match is, of course, Ushijima.

423
00:20:43.880 --> 00:20:47.640
We need an anti-Ushijima strategy first,
 or we don't stand a chance.

424
00:20:48.210 --> 00:20:51.620
And for that, we need to 
break down our opponents.

425
00:20:48.560 --> 00:20:50.760
Asahi, nice serve!

426
00:20:51.620 --> 00:20:54.920
We need to just keep serving up 
powerful attacks, one after another.

427
00:20:59.520 --> 00:21:01.190
All right! It's off!

428
00:21:01.890 --> 00:21:02.920
Ushijima-san!

429
00:21:06.610 --> 00:21:08.080
All right!

430
00:21:07.060 --> 00:21:08.080
it...

431
00:21:08.080 --> 00:21:09.330
Don't mind! Don't mind!

432
00:21:09.700 --> 00:21:11.000
Even if they get a point,

433
00:21:11.000 --> 00:21:13.670
we just have to keep doing 
what we just did, right?

434
00:21:13.670 --> 00:21:14.420
Yeah.

435
00:21:15.070 --> 00:21:16.080
Ugh.

436
00:21:16.380 --> 00:21:18.790
That guy's serving again.

437
00:21:21.080 --> 00:21:22.650
Wakatoshi, nice serve!

438
00:21:31.600 --> 00:21:33.160
It's just as I planned!

439
00:21:33.160 --> 00:21:34.520
You're tearing up.

440
00:21:34.520 --> 00:21:37.480
Shiratorizawa           Karasuno

441
00:21:34.920 --> 00:21:36.010
Well done, Tanaka!

442
00:21:36.010 --> 00:21:37.480
All right. They're keeping up.

443
00:21:37.960 --> 00:21:42.690
If they can get used to Ushiwaka's left-handedness,
 they have a chance at winning.

444
00:21:43.460 --> 00:21:46.820
I'm gonna go show Ushiwaka who's boss!

445
00:21:46.820 --> 00:21:49.490
Did something happen with 
Hinata and Ushiwaka?

446
00:21:49.490 --> 00:21:52.220
Apparently they had some kind of scuffle.

447
00:21:52.220 --> 00:21:56.160
What?! He keeps causing trouble with 
other schools without us knowing.

448
00:21:59.670 --> 00:22:01.270
Don't hold back.

449
00:22:00.100 --> 00:22:01.270
Bring it!

450
00:22:01.270 --> 00:22:03.570
Just keep on attacking.

451
00:22:03.570 --> 00:22:05.700
That's the only strategy we have.

452
00:22:07.840 --> 00:22:09.080
Chance ball!

453
00:22:10.720 --> 00:22:12.890
Give it to me!

454
00:22:12.890 --> 00:22:14.470
It's that diagonal jump again!

455
00:22:34.310 --> 00:22:36.400
If you want to beat Wakatoshi-kun,

456
00:22:36.400 --> 00:22:38.500
you're gonna have to beat me, first.

457
00:22:38.500 --> 00:22:39.750
Ya know?

458
00:24:13.890 --> 00:24:16.680
The more that Wakatoshi-kun gets attention,

459
00:24:16.680 --> 00:24:20.060
the more impactful it is when I appear.

460
00:24:20.060 --> 00:24:22.080
Tendo-san, your personality 
really is trash.

461
00:24:22.080 --> 00:24:23.640
Stop! No spoilers!

462
00:24:22.440 --> 00:24:26.980
Episode 03: GUESS-MONSTER

463
00:24:24.030 --> 00:24:26.440
Next time on Haikyu!!: "GUESS-MONSTER."
